Libraries:  Opus (snapshot) / Opus-tools (snapshot) / libogg 1.3
Imported:   August 8th, 2012

Steps taken to adapt original opus/opus-tool/ogg source files to rockbox
(useful when for example syncing a new snapshot)

Opus:
* copy files from opus/src/ and opus/include/ to lib/rbcodec/codecs/libopus
* copy files from opus/celt to lib/rbcodec/codecs/libopus/celt
* copy files from opus/silk to lib/rbcodec/codecs/libopus/silk
* rename opus config.h file to opus_config.h and replace #include "config.h",
  for example
find . -name "*.h" -print | xargs sed -i 's/include "config.h"/include "opus_config.h"/g'
find . -name "*.c" -print | xargs sed -i 's/include "config.h"/include "opus_config.h"/g'

Opus-tools:
* copy src/opus_header.h and src/opus_header.c to lib/rbcodec/codecs/libopus

Ogg:
* copy libogg/src/framing.c to lib/rbcodec/codecs/libopus/ogg
* copy libogg/include/ogg.h to lib/rbcodec/codecs/libopus/ogg
* changed #include "ogg/ogg.h" to #include "ogg.h" in framing.c
* added os_config.h to lib/rbcodec/codecs/libopus/ogg

